    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-11-10T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-11-10T13:00:00-05:00" n="395"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d395">
                <head>395. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Delegation at the Foreign Ministers
                        Meetings</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d395fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 396.1–GE/11–1055. Top Secret; Limit Distribution. Received at 7:52
                        p.m.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>,<date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-11-10T19:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 10, 1955—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 242.</p>
                <p>. . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Gijeon Raphael of Israel Foreign Ministry, who is currently in Geneva for liaison
                    during quadripartite conference, told member <gloss target="#t_USDel1"
                        >USDel</gloss> today that <gloss target="#t_IG1">IG</gloss> has as its
                    objective overthrow of <persName corresp="#p_NNNGA1">Nasser</persName> regime.
                    Also expressed confidence that if Soviets should receive cooperation from
                    government of any other Arab States it would be able bring <pb facs="0756"
                        n="728" xml:id="pg_728"/> about their overthrow also by the expression
                        <gloss target="#t_IG1">IG</gloss>’s firm opposition to efforts of tripartite
                    powers to sense cooperation of <persName corresp="#p_NNNGA1">Nasser</persName>
                    regime.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
